## Key Findings
Conclusions. Thus, sleep impairments and behavioral 
dysfunction have mutual inﬂ uences. Sleep changes described 
in ADHD are generally not speciﬁ c and are mostly linked 
with maturation of the sleep mechanism. This reﬂ ects deep 
impairments in the formation of the integrative functions of 
the brain, including the integrative mechanisms of sleep and 
chronobiological processes in ontogeny.
 
